<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,457,1627,1653]" box="[189,457,1627,1653]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,457,1627,1653]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,457,1627,1653]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1398,1674,1806]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Species with yellow face with a medial black vitta, scutum black with a continuous lateral yellow vitta from postpronotum to scutellum, scutellum yellow with a median black macula, terga 2 and 5 with two lateral yellow maculae and terga 3 and 4 with a broad yellow fascia. It differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1944" box="[1177,1339,1745,1771]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Allograpta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripilosa">
<emphasis box="[1177,1339,1745,1771]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">A. nigripilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only in the wing microtrichia, as stated in the key.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
